The antimicrobial activity of the essential oils of
apparently related to its terpenes type components such
as pinene, myrcene and limonene (Table 1), since there is
a relationship between the chemical structures of the most
abundant oils and their antimicrobial activities. Limonene
has been shown to have strong antifungal properties [38].
Although the mechanism of action of terpenes is not fully
understood, it is thought to involve membrane disruption
by the lipophilic compounds [39]. The essential oils con-
